properties.sfomuseum:description: a. Airmail flight cover, FAM-19, part of first airmail service between United States and New Zealand, San Francisco - Canton Island route; blue stamped cachet at left, “United States Airmail; First flight FAM 19; South Pacific service”; postmarked July 12, 1940 in San Francisco with four-line cancellation mark over 10-cent and 20-cent stamps; no backstamp.b. Backing sheet with two sets of mounting corners, with handwritten caption: “July 1940, New Pan Am route (FAM 19) - U.S. to New Zealand and Australia”, and black and white photographic image of Boeing 314 in flight.
